luamenu - lua scripted menu
===========================
luamenu is a fork of dmenu, dynamic menu for dwm, which adds lua
scripting amongst other things.

See suckless.org for more details on dmenu.


Requirements
------------
In order to build luamenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (luamenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install luamenu (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running luamenu
---------------
See the man page for details.
